# FlowOS core context

**Product:** Personal daily productivity OS (tasks, habits, focus, schedule, reflection, notes).  
**Production:** https://flowos-sage.vercel.app  
**Stack:** Next.js App Router, React, TypeScript, Tailwind, Supabase. Repo root = app root.

**Current milestone:** M2 Founder Daily Driver (see `docs/execution/README.md`).

## Doc authority (conflicts — higher wins)

1. `docs/strategy/flowos-vision-and-product-strategy.md` — product vision, philosophy, positioning (highest)
2. `docs/execution/logs/decision-log.md` — dated decisions (explicit amendments win for that change)
3. `docs/strategy/execution-masterplan.md`
4. `docs/foundation/governance/` (PRINCIPLES, GATES, QUALITY, ENGINEERING, CODE_STANDARDS, GIT_WORKFLOW)
5. `docs/foundation/` + `docs/execution/`
6. `docs/archive/` — history only; never for current planning

## Do not use for current work

- `docs/archive/design/` except `july-3/` for history
- Superseded roadmaps / launch plans — use execution masterplan

## Working norms

- **Runbook session:** read `docs/execution/runbooks/m2-founder-daily-driver.md`; new branch per session; see `git-workflow.mdc`
- **UI/UX idea:** `docs/execution/logs/inbox.md` first
- **Product decision:** append `decision-log.md`
- **After merge to main:** `docs/execution/logs/july-log.md`
- **Scope:** M2 closed scope only — no command palette, new modules, monolith refactors unless runbook says so

## Code truth

Prefer `docs/foundation/FEATURE_INVENTORY.md` + codebase over archived project-state docs.
